    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Spring Applied Hydraulically Released (SAHR) Park Brake Canister</title>
        <para>The SAHR canister is located inside the driver's side frame rail, just forward of the rear axle (see
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404815">FIGURE 16</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404816">FIGURE 17</hotlnk>). The SAHR canister is the component that controls the tension
            applied to the parking brake cable. Internal springs are used to apply tension to the parking brake cable,
            which applies the parking brake. When pressurized brake fluid is routed to the SAHR canister, hydraulic
            pressure overcomes the internal springs to relax the parking brake cable, which releases the parking brake.
        </para>
